Then, on the daily timeline, he drops each item (as the item code) onto the timeline roughly where he will do it for the day. 
Then as he completes items during the day, he marks them off the list, and they get marked off the timeline as well. 

Items that dont get completed automactilly get moved to the next day with a little label indicating they were carried. 

So the final step will be a timeline. Users should be able to select items on either the timeline or the list and re-schedle them (to the day, not on the days individual timeline). 

EACH DAY HAS A PILE. Tasks not done each day get automatically added to the next days pile, then they will go through the same Pile, Shape, Fill pattern on the next day. 


THIS IS THE MAIN FLOW WE SHOULD IMPLEMENT:
So start the day with a pile which is everything left over from yesterday or scheduled for that day
Then you add any new items for the day
then you go to shape, and decide what action (5 filters) needs to be taken for that a (or not take)
Then finally you get to your fill page. This shows your daily planner, and allows you to drag and drop your items still in your pile onto the daily planner to make a schedule. At the end of the day, items not completed are added to the unfiltered pile for the next day to repeat the task. 